member.param:
A Rect object that defines rectangle coordinates.
The ranges of coordinates is as follows:
Left:	0-375;
Top:	0-239;
Right:	376-751;
Bottom:	240-479;
This rectangular image region must overlap with at least part of the
decoded symbol in order to be considered a valid decode.

member.summary:
Get/Set the desired decode mode.
The three modes are standard, reduced omni-directional
and aggressive linear;

Width of image in IntellBarcodeUnits;
Must be a multiple of 4, otherwise the control will force it to a
multiple of 4 for display compatibility.

member.remarks:
When comparing the trigger key to the KeyCode parameter in
            KeyUp or KeyDown events, it must be cast to (Keys): e.g.
            if (e.KeyCode == (Keys)ctlImage.TriggerKey)

member.example:
If visual AutoScan property is set true, it is recommended that the
following exception checking logic be added to detect the case where
the Trigger Key is already reserved.

try
{
	InitializeComponent();
}
catch(ApplicationException e)
{
	MessageBox.Show(e.Message, "Application Exception");
	Application.Exit();
}

member.summary:
The custom DecodeException class is derived from the standard Exception 
class and is used to identify errors that occur in the decode control. 
Decode Exceptions can be caught to help provide detailed information 
regarding errors that may occur within the application related to scanning.
Below is an example using the DecodeException class.

try
{
    oDecodeControl.ScanBarcode();
}
catch (DecodeException dex)
{
    MessageBox.Show(dex.Message);
}
